HEADWORD: Sweetbrier
<hw>Sweet"bri`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A kind of rose (<spn>Rosa rubiginosa</spn>) with minutely glandular
and fragrant foliage. The small-flowered sweetbrier is <spn>Rosa
micrantha</spn>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sweeten</ent>⟦br⟧
